seal     : When your best move depends on what the other player does — and theirs on you — you've left simple decision-making and entered a game. Game theory is the mathematics of that bind: rivals, allies, bluffs, and threats reduced to payoffs and equilibria. It explains why two rational players can both choose to lose, and how cooperation can survive in a world built to punish it.
